s regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":25,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Hendower was born in 1430, in Cornwall, England. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Thomas Tregarthen. She died on 14 April 1500, at the age of 70, and was buried in Cornwall, England."},"et":{"1430–14 April 1500":"1430–14. aprill 1500","1429–1508":"1429–1508","1464–1505":"1464–1505","1478–1503":"1478–1503","1430–1500":"1430–1500","1503":"1503","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1464":"1464","1430":"1430","14 April 1500":"14. aprill 1500","1508":"1508","1429":"1429","1505":"1505","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1430–14 April 1500":"1430–14. huhtikuuta 1500","1429–1508":"1429–1508","1464–1505":"1464–1505","1478–1503":"1478–1503","1430–1500":"1430–1500","1503":"1503","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1464":"1464","1430":"1430","14 April 1500":"14. huhtikuuta 1500","1508":"1508","1429":"1429","1505":"1505","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1430–14 April 1500":"1430–14 avril 1500","1429–1508":"1429–1508","1464–1505":"1464–1505","1478–1503":"1478–1503","1430–1500":"1430–1500","1503":"1503","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1464":"1464","1430":"1430","14 April 1500":"14 avril 1500","1508":"1508","1429